column5: Hit a couple of eastern tribs on Tuesday trying to subside my craving for chrome. First trib we stopped at.... totally frozen Another... high and muddy. So we went to a sure fire place and it payed off. morning bite was good, and around 11 am water became too stained and fish shut off. For the day, we landed 4 and lost just as many. It was a great day to be out! Myself with a nice one..
Nice fish! glad to see your getting some steel, them bullets sure are fun
Nice chromes dude! Are you in for the BOQ next weekend?
Thanks guys! Yeah it's a popular spot, and when the conditions are right, can be fantastic. I'm in for the BOQ trip Grant I'll contact you about it. Jon
